New York's Subway,
   Bus Fares Rise 8.7%
The new fare took effect at 12:01 EST yesterday. Token
sales were limited to four tokens before the new fare took
effect. The MTA said tokens now in use will be replaced at a
later date. The authority had threatened to raise fares to
$1.40 to close a $263 million budget gap. Even with the new
fare and the $90 million transfer, the transit system will be
short $67 million.